spell = Spell.create(name: "Otiluke's Resilient Sphere", level: 4, school_id: evocation.id, casting_time: "1 action", range: "30 feet", duration: "Concentration, up to 1 minute", short_description: "1 crea/obj up to Large Dex save or enclosed in impenetrable sphere; can be moved as hamsterball", description: "A sphere of shimmering force encloses a creature or object o f Large size or smaller within range. An unwilling creature must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is enclosed for the duration. Nothing not physical objects, energy, or other spell effects can pass through the barrier, in or out, though a creature in the sphere can breathe there. The sphere is immune to all damage, and a creature or object inside can't be damaged by attacks or effects originating from outside, nor can a creature inside the sphere damage anything outside it. The sphere is weightless and just large enough to contain the creature or object inside. An enclosed creature can use its action to push against the sphere's walls and thus roll the sphere at up to half the creature's speed. Similarly, the globe can be picked up and moved by other creatures. A disintegrate spell targeting the globe destroys it without harming anything inside it.", v: true, s: true, m: true, r: false, material: "a hemispherical piece of clear crystal and a matching hemispherical piece of gum arabic")
Mastery.create(spell_id: spell.id, dnd_class_id: wizard.id)
spell = Spell.create(name: "Otto's Irresistible Dance", level: 6, school_id: enchantment.id, casting_time: "1 action", range: "30 feet", duration: "Concentration, up to 1 minute", short_description: "1 crea dances in place, can’t move, dis. on attacks/Dex saves, adv. on atks vs. target; Wis save each rnd", description: "Choose one creature that you can see within range. The target begins a comic dance in place: shuffling, tapping its feet, and capering for the duration. Creatures that can't be charmed are immune to this spell. A dancing creature must use all its movement to dance without leaving its space and has disadvantage on Dexterity saving throws and attack rolls. While the target is affected by this spell, other creatures have advantage on attack rolls against it. As an action, a dancing creature makes a Wisdom saving throw to regain control o f itself. On a successful save, the spell ends.", v: true, s: false, m: false, r: false)
