spell = Spell.create(name: "Wall of Force", level: 5, school_id: evocation.id, casting_time: "1 action", range: "120 feet", duration: "Concentration, up to 10 minutes", short_description: "10 10×10-ft panels or 10-ft rad (hemi)sphere invisible, impenetrable wall; can float in air; see book", description: "  An invisible wall of force springs into existence at a point you choose within range. The wall appears in any orientation you choose, as a horizontal or vertical barrier or at an angle. It can be free floating or resting on a solid surface. You can form it into a hemispherical dome or a sphere with a radius of up to 10 feet, or you can shape a flat surface made up of ten 10-foot-by-10-foot panels. Each panel must be continguous with another panel. In any form, the wall is 1/4 inch thick. It lasts for the duration. If the wall cuts through a creature's space when it appears, the creature is pushed to one side of the wall (your choice which side).   Nothing can physically pass through the wall. It is immune to all damage and can't be dispelled by dispel magic. A disintegrate spell destroys the wall instantly, however.  The wall also extends into the Ethereal Plane, blocking ethereal travel through the wall.", v: true, s: true, m: true, r: false, material: "a pinch of powder made by crushing a clear gemstone")
